{
  "texts": [
    "The question is important because it is considered one of the key issues raised in terms of simulating ToM in an AI model.",
    "According to Cognitive Appraisal Theory, our thoughts are what create our emotions.",
    "This view states that our emotions are largely determined by how we sometimes interpret or evaluate situations.",
    "Cognitive appraisal could occur unconsciously, as suggested by James and Lange [34], or consciously, as suggested by Schachter and Singer [35].",
    "For example, if we encounter an aggressive dog while walking down the street and think ''I am in danger, '' the appraisal of this situation may lead to feelings of fear or anxiety."
  ]
}